                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Pither: he keeps the kings, Arms, Ranelagh-road, Thames-bank. The prisoner was our pot-boy—he came, on the 3rd of May, and told me that Mrs. Copeland wanted change for a <hi rend="italic">£5 note</hi>—I gave him four sovereigns, and 1<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. in silver—he went away, and I saw him no more till he was taken—I sent for Mrs. Copeland, and she had not seen him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I bought some clothes and other things with the money, and was on my way down to lpswich, where I belong.</p>
